yN_HQ5vm7nk.keywords: bettyskitchen you tube vlog Betty Betty's Kitchen video recipe recipes salted pie filling milk cornstarch flour sugar sea salt eggs whipped topping Cool Whip brown light cream half and half butter vanilla perfect best ever Kentucky YouTube's homestyle homemade home made style stove top stovetop cook bake oven baking Southern comfort food cooking youtube channel family friends brunch lunch party supper dinner entertain entertaining dessert snack sweet treat caramel puddingBetty's Salted Caramel PuddingBetty demonstrates how to make Salted Caramel Pudding. This pudding has a delicious flavor and a light, airy texture. Salted Caramel Pudding  cup light brown sugar, firmly packed 1 ounce light cream or halfandhalf 1 tablespoon butter  teaspoon vanilla extract 1  tablespoons cornstarch 1  tablespoons flour 1  tablespoons white sugar 2  ounces additional milk 2 eggs 1 quart additional milk 18 teaspoon coarse sea salt 1 cup whipped topping Cool Whip additional sea salt for topping In a small saucepan, make a caramel mixture as follows Bring brown sugar, light cream, butter, and vanilla to a boil over low to medium heat. Without stirring, boil over low heat for about 8 minutes. Set aside to cool. In a large bowl, mix cornstarch, flour, and sugar. Add 2  ounces milk very slowly, stirring until mixture is smooth. Add eggs and beat well with a mixer on medium speed. Heat 1 quart milk in a medium saucepan until hot, but not boiling. Add a small amount of the hot mixture to the beaten egg mixture and then pour the egg mixture into the hot milk, stirring well. Stir in about 18 teaspoon coarse sea salt. Set aside to cool for about 15 minutes. Stir in the caramel mixture. Place on stove and cook over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture is thick and bubbly. Cool at room temperature for about an hour. Then, refrigerate for at least 4 hours, stirring occasionally while cooling, until mixture is of pudding consistency. Fold in whipped topping, cover with plastic wrap, and refrigerate until ready to serve. To serve, spoon pudding into sherbet glasses. Sprinkle top of each with a small amount of coarse sea salt. Enjoy! I hope you love this recipe! QlL0rwOcLIE.keywords: boston more than a feeling BostonBand rocksmith classic rock xbox 360 guitar gaming music gaming ytstretch169Rocksmith  Boston  More Than A Feeling ComboIt seems like noone records Combo 1 for this song. It's the better of the two arrangements,in my opinion, so I threw up a run of my own. The two solos are in Combo 2, meaning they ARE NOT in this video. This is probably my proudest Rocksmith achievement so far. I set a goal in July to get this arrangement 100 leveled and to play it pretty well. I think I've accomplished that but some of my transitions could use a bit more practice. Moving to that Bm chord gives me a bit of trouble too. I'd say this song is my favorite in RS so far. Combo 2 has the solos in it which is probably why its more popular to record but I think this one is funner and sounds better. This arrangement is definitely the harder of the two and it took quite a bit of practice in Riff Repeater to get everything close to memorized. I am NOT using the default tone Mass Drive for this song. There are several songs in RS that sound terrible with the default tone and this is one of them. There's WAY too much distortion in it for my tastes so I made a custom one Bahston. The chorus  I think that's what it's called, starts at 039 sounds a little meh with mine but it's too much of a hassle to try and change tones during the song. Kinda wish I had a way to get a "Hand Cam" thing going. Sort of like what Elison and some other RS recorders have done. That probably would have been neat for this one.

The soundtrack was eventually released in four parts  Original Soundtrack Volume 1  A 2CD set containing mainly the softer and orchestral pieces from the game.  Original Soundtrack Volume 2  Another 2CD set containing the upbeat music, primarily the battle and dungeon themes.  Arrange Album  A selection of tracks from the game reworked in different styles.  Voice Mix  Similar to the Arrange Album, but featuring dialogue sampled from the Japanese version of the game along with the music. The limited edition of Volume 1 also came with a box to hold all four albums. When the game was revised into the Director's Cut, Sakuraba composed a few new pieces of music and released an album for them.
